      • isDivergedFromBasis

        boolean isDivergedFromBasis()
        Returns whether or not this component has diverged from its current basis. It will have diverged from the basis if there additional change sets on top of the baseline, or if this component has the same change sets as the baseline, but has them in a different order.
        Since:
        0.12.0.3 (EWM 7.0.3)

      • isHierarchyDivergedFromBasis

        boolean isHierarchyDivergedFromBasis()
        Returns whether or not the component hierarchy rooted at this component has diverged from its hierarchical baseline. If this component is not the root of a hierarchy, then this is equivalent to isDivergedFromBasis() The hierarchy will have diverged if: - isDivergedFromBasis() returns true for this component, or any subcomponent in its hierarchy. - the basis of any subcomponent does not match the hierarchical baseline which is the basis of this component. - any components have been added or removed as compared to the hierarchical basis of this component.
        Returns:
